    <h1 > <b ></b>THE SUPER HERO </b> </h1>
        <h2> Hanumaan</h2>
        <p> Hanuman, the Monkey God, is typically depicted with distinctive physical attributes in Hindu iconography. His appearance carries symbolic and mythological significance. Here's an explanation of Hanuman's physical appearance:  </p>

    <ol>
    <li>    Monkey-Faced: </li>
    <p> Hanuman is invariably depicted with the face of a monkey, which is one of his most defining features. His monkey face signifies his lineage as a Vanara (a race of monkey-like beings) and symbolizes his agility, intelligence, and resourcefulness. </p>
    <li> Muscular Body:  </li>
    <p> Hanuman is often portrayed with a robust and muscular physique, emphasizing his immense strength and physical prowess. His muscular form represents his capability to perform extraordinary feats</p>
    <li> Orange or Reddish-Brown Complexion: </li>
    <p> Hanuman's body is typically depicted with an orange or reddish-brown complexion. This color symbolizes his association with Lord Shiva, as red or orange is often associated with asceticism and renunciation.</p>
    </ol>
